        "header": "Appendix 0.CInference Time Analysis",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2606.05102/2606.05102v1/x67.png",
                "caption": "Figure 11:Inference cost vs. input views.(a) Forward pass time and (b) peak GPU memory.\nThe backbone dominates at all view counts; token compression and Gaussian decoding remain negligible.\nThe view-dependent schedule (r=12​2/Nr{=}\\tfrac{1}{2}\\sqrt{2/N}) keeps memory within 24 GB even at 192 views, wherer=1.0r{=}1.0approaches the hardware limit.\nWe show YoNoSplat[40]for reference.",
                "position": 2188
            },
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2606.05102/2606.05102v1/x68.png",
                "caption": "Figure 12:Output representation efficiency.(a) Rendering speed and (b) Gaussian storage.\nUnder fixed ratios, Gaussian count grows linearly with views; view-dependent scaling merges redundant cross-view observations, keeping storage nearly flat.\nAt 192 views, scaled compression delivers a10×10{\\times}rendering speedup with20×20{\\times}less storage.\nWe show YoNoSplat[40]for reference.",
                "position": 2195
            }
        ]
    },
